## Demographics

As of March 31, 2017, Garzeno has a population of 765 inhabitants, resulting in a population density of approximately 26.6 inhabitants per square kilometer (68.9 inhabitants per square mile). This relatively low population density underscores the rural and tranquil nature of the municipality, offering a peaceful retreat from the hustle and bustle of urban life.

### Population Statistics

The demographic composition of Garzeno reflects a blend of long-standing residents and newcomers drawn to the area's natural beauty and serene environment. The municipality's population has remained relatively stable over the years, with a slight trend towards an aging population, common in many rural areas of Italy.

